        "args": {
            "message": "Rankings of the latest technology developments on December 23, 2023, for Instagram appeal:\n1. Apple’s Vision Pro mixed-reality headset announcement, a potential game-changer. - High potential for visual representation and excitement about new technology.\n2. AI took centre stage with robots creating art and AI assistants crafting haikus, promising growth in 2024. - High engagement due to the visual and creative aspects of AI.\n3. OpenAI’s ChatGPT vs Google’s Bard in the AI battle of generative AI platforms. - General popularity and the debate may drive user interaction.\n4. Elon Musk’s dominant presence in tech discussions, rebranding Twitter as X. - Elon Musk’s polarizing influence is likely to engage users firmly.\n5. Increased notoriety of deepfakes, particularly involving Indian celebrities. - Potential for visual content but may also instigate a serious discussion about cybersecurity.\n6. The EU’s push for Apple to transit iPhones to Type-C. - While important, might lack visual appeal and immediate engagement.\n7. Surge in online scams with an increasing digital lifestyle. - Generally does not contain elements that drive high engagement on visual platforms like Instagram.",
